strategy.reasoning: Keep the main version, remove converted/working variants

rules.reason: Base files are typically the most stable

phase1.name: Validation Phase
steps: Check all recommended KEEP files exist
Run syntax validation on KEEP files
Test sample execution of key tests
safetyChecks: No critical tests in REMOVE list

phase2.name: Safe Backup Phase
steps: Copy all REMOVE files to backup location

phase3.name: Deduplication Phase
steps: Remove duplicate files in order of safety

phase4.name: Validation & Testing Phase
steps: Execute sample from each risk category

low: Duplicate removal is reversible with backups
Test IDs are unique (no ID conflicts)
File patterns are predictable and systematic
medium: Some tests might have subtle differences
Configuration files might reference removed tests
high: Manual review needed for critical tests
Full regression testing recommended after cleanup

recommendations: Start with Phase 1 validation to ensure safety
Create comprehensive backups before any removal
Remove files gradually, testing after each batch
Have rollback plan ready in case of issues
